<subSubSection id="94CCDDF07543FFC2DFF44CE7FA75FBF4" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DC698E7B7543FFC2DFF44CE7FA75FBF4" blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DFF44CE7FEA4FE10" bold="true" box="[199,322,476,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
New species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DD554CE6FC06FE10" authority="(Haan, 1842)" authorityName="Haan" authorityYear="1842" baseAuthorityName="De Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[614,992,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DD554CE6FCA3FE10" box="[614,837,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">Criotettix japonicus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B847F38A7543FFC2DC674CE6FC31FE10" author="Haan, W. de" box="[852,983,477,503]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" pagination="45 - 124" refId="ref12819" refString="Haan, W. de. (1842). In: Temminck [ed.]. Verhandelingen over de Natuurlijke Geschiedenis der Nederlansche Overzeesche Bezittingen. de Leden der Natuurkundige Commissie in Indie en andere Schrijvers, 16, 45 - 124" type="journal article" year="1842">Haan, 1842</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from which it differs in width of vertex 1.2 times wider than width of one eye in female (width of vertex 2.0 times wider than width of one eye in female in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DFA44F1EFEC3FDD8" baseAuthorityName="De Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[151,293,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DFA44F1EFEC3FDD8" box="[151,293,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); length of a segment in middle of antenna about 5–6 times longer than its width (length of a segment in middle of antenna about 2 times longer than its width in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DC0C4F72FC28FD84" baseAuthorityName="De Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[831,974,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DC0C4F72FC28FD84" box="[831,974,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); abbreviated carinae between shoulders inconspicuous or absent (with a pair of abbreviated carinae between shoulders); caudal end of pronotum surpassing apex of hind tibia (caudal end of pronotum reaching two-thirds of hind tibia). It appears similar also to 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DA024FAAFDEDFD28" authority="Zheng &amp; Ou, 2003" authorityName="Zheng &amp; Ou" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DA024FAAFEC7FD28" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">Criotettix yunnanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B847F38A7543FFC2DE1F4F8EFDEDFD28" author="Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Ou, X. H." box="[300,523,693,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" pagination="673 - 678" refId="ref13888" refString="Zheng, Z. M. &amp; Ou, X. H. (2003) Four new species of Scelimenidae from Yunnan province (Orthoptera, Tetrigoidea). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 28 (4), 673 - 678." type="journal article" year="2003">Zheng &amp; Ou, 2003</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by lateral carinae of prozona constricted backwards (lateral keels of prozona parallel in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DD154FE2FD37FD14" box="[550,721,729,755]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DD154FE2FD37FD14" box="[550,721,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); posterior angles of lateral lobes of pronotum with long spines (posterior angles of lateral lobes of pronotum acute and subspiniform in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DCEA4FC6FB60FCF0" box="[985,1158,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DCEA4FC6FB60FCF0" box="[985,1158,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); upper margin of hind femur finely serrated and with a slightly large tooth before antegenicular (upper margin of hind femur smooth in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DAB04E1AFEC7FCB8" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DAB04E1AFEC7FCB8" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). It appears similar also to 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DD6B4E7EFC00FCB8" authority="(Walker, 1871)" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1871" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[600,998,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armigera">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DD6B4E7EFCD5FCB8" box="[600,819,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">Criotettix armigera</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="B847F38A7543FFC2DC704E7EFC3BFCB8" author="Walker, F." box="[835,989,837,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" pagination="811 - 850" refId="ref13374" refString="Walker, F. (1871) Catalogue of the Specimens of Dermaptera Saltatoria in the Collection of the British Museum. Part V. Department of Zoology, British Museum (Natural History), London, pp. 811 - 850" type="book chapter" year="1871">Walker, 1871</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the latter by head not exserted above pronotal surface (head exserted above pronotal surface in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DCE84E52FB83FC64" box="[987,1125,873,899]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armigera">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DCE84E52FB83FC64" box="[987,1125,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. armigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); width of vertex 1.2 times wider than width of one eye in female (width of vertex equal to or narrower than width of one eye in female in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DAB04EB6FF19FC2C" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armigera">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DAB04EB6FF19FC2C" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. armigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); abbreviated carinae between shoulders inconspicuous or absent (with a pair of abbreviated carinae between shoulders in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DE5C4EEEFE11FC08" box="[367,503,981,1007]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armigera">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DE5C4EEEFE11FC08" box="[367,503,981,1007]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. armigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); length of posterior angles spines of lateral lobes of pronotum longer than width of vertex (length of posterior angles spines of lateral lobes of pronotum shorter than width of vertex in 
<taxonomicName id="1BD6F5F87543FFC2DBCA4EC2FA64FBF4" box="[1273,1410,1017,1043]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Criotettix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="armigera">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DBCA4EC2FA64FBF4" box="[1273,1410,1017,1043]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">C. armigera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="94CCDDF07543FFC2DFF44926FE0FFBBC" pageId="9" pageNumber="507" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="DC698E7B7543FFC2DFF44926FE0FFBBC" blockId="9.[151,1437,153,1151]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DFF44926FEA9FBD0" bold="true" box="[199,335,1053,1079]" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is derived from “ 
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DDC64926FCC1FBD0" box="[757,807,1053,1079]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">long</emphasis>
” and “ 
<emphasis id="EEA252697543FFC2DC454925FC58FBD0" box="[886,958,1054,1079]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="507">spinus</emphasis>
”, meaning posterior angles of lateral lobes of pronotum with long spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
